parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tread Separation and Loss of Traction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tread separation and loss of traction can cause accidents, especially in rainy conditions, leading to vehicle damage, injury, or even fatalities.
symptoms: Sliding or loss of control on the road
and wobbling or vibration of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Broken Bolt in Clutch Pedal Assembly
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A broken bolt in the clutch pedal assembly can cause the clutch pedal to malfunction, leading to difficulty shifting gears, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels loose or wobbly
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
unusual noises or vibrations when pressing the clutch pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion and loosening of the wheel can cause a loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to wheel detachment while driving, which can result in serious injuries or fatalities.
A malfunctioning seat belt can fail to restrain the driver in the event of sudden stops, accidents, or crashes, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt will not lock in place
the seat belt is loose or cannot be tightened
the seat belt buckle does not click or latch properly
the seat belt warning light is illuminated on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust manifold gasket can cause the engine to run rough, lose power, and potentially overheat, leading to decreased vehicle performance and increased risk of engine damage.
